Subject: Submit: Aditum Bio =96 Vice President, Clinical Development - Immu=
nology - Benjamin Hoehn MD,Ph.D

Hi Maura,

Benjamin Hoehn, MD, PhD is currently Clinical Development Lead at Annexon B=
iosciences with 15+ years total industry experience and 5+ years focused on=
 immunology and autoimmune/rare disease clinical development. He holds an M=
D/PhD from Stanford and has extensive early-stage immunology expertise, hav=
ing led Phase 1 SAD/MAD, Phase 2 POC, and Phase 3 programs in autoimmune an=
d neuroinflammatory indications (GBS, ALS, IMNM, CAD, MG). At Annexon, he's=
 currently leading the Phase 3 GBS program toward BLA submission (authoring=
 Modules 2 & 5) while simultaneously executing FIH studies. He's proven he =
can independently run multiple complex programs with minimal oversight. His=
 regulatory experience includes FDA/EMA/PMDA submissions, EOP2 meetings, an=
d multiple IND authorships. He contributed to FDA approval of istradefyllin=
e at Kyowa Kirin and has built global trial networks including the Internat=
ional GBS Outcomes Study group.

Hoehn is drawn to Aditum's mission to accelerate transformative medicines t=
hrough early clinical development and sees this as an ideal platform to app=
ly his translational expertise across a broader immunology portfolio. He is=
 seeking a VP Clinical Development title, $440K base salary (open to consid=
eration of total compensation package). He would work out of the Oakland of=
fice, 5 days/week (prefers in-office over remote).


Benjamin Hoehn, MD, PhD

  *
Clinical Development Lead, Neurodegeneration Programs, Annexon Biosciences
  *
MD and PhD (Neuroscience), Stanford University; BA Neuroscience, Pomona Col=
lege; Neurosurgery Residency, University of Virginia
  *
15+ years in biotech/pharma; 5+ years in immunology/autoimmune clinical dev=
elopment
  *   Leading Phase 3 GBS program at Annexon toward BLA submission with FDA=
/EMA briefing books and Module 2 & 5 authoring
  *   Directed Phase 1 SAD/MAD and Phase 2 POC studies in neuroinflammatory=
/autoimmune disorders
  *   Led ALS and IMNM programs at UCB (Phase 2/3 and Phase 3) including EO=
P2 FDA meetings and IND submissions
  *   Contributed to FDA approval of istradefylline at Kyowa Kirin (2019)
  *   Authored 4 INDs and directed 15+ clinical studies as Consultant CMO a=
t NextScience
  *   Built global trial networks spanning US, Europe, Bangladesh, and Aust=
ria
  *
Early-stage clinical development (pre-IND, IND, Phase 1-2, POC); Immunology=
/autoimmune expertise (ALS, GBS, IMNM, CAD, MG); Regulatory strategy (FDA, =
EMA, PMDA); Translational medicine and biomarker-driven trial design; Safet=
y oversight and medical monitoring; Global trial leadership and CRO/vendor =
management

Best,
Bryan


